title: The SpaceX Falcon 9 Launch Update
article: On March 31st, 2024, the SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket took off. The rocket launched from California Space Coast, aiming to put 23 satellites in orbit. The launch was delayed due to bad weather conditions. The original liftoff was scheduled at 7:16pm March 30th. The first stage of the Falcon 9 will be brought back to the original launch pad. The next launch is scheduled to be sometime in June.
author: Julian Boryshansky
